Comment:
Hi everyone!

Right now, in the middle of a Big Freeze, we are all getting ready for Christmas.  Well, here is a little winter-warmer for you.  This is now Expert Draw No. 12 and if Dave, my opponent had just 17 points more on his rating it would have been my third Master Draw.  Still, I am pleased with the result as I got canned by Dave with the black pieces.  So, how did all this come about?  Well, read on.  Gameknot analysis is provided with the following link:http://gameknot.com/analyze-board.pl?bd=14973101&rnd=0.09016686302708665

15. Bb5 - Fou Leblanc moves to try and stop Re8 and offers another exchange of queens.  Black could keep the Witch on the g1-a7 diagonal but Glenda can get in a nice nuisance check on the a3-f8 diagonal.  Black moves his queen onto the e column threatening Qe1# but Henry decided to rid himself of black's dsb.

17. Ke1 - If it were not for the fact that the Wicked Witch of the West can check Henry ad infinitum on the e and f files I would be looking forward to my first ever Expert Victory in a non-timed out game with an 8 point material advantage.  However, Dave does have Ye Olde Perpetualle up his sleeve so I offered him a draw and he accepted.  Gameknot Analysis seemed to back up my decision.
